    "comment_id" : 1937628,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "Be aware that for <i>most</i> classes there really is nothing interesting to say about the type parameter, because the type parameter is essentially defined by how it appears in the methods of the object. I&#39;d skip <code>@param &lt;T&gt;</code> most of the time and only use it when it&#39;s really not clear."
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 11089,
