    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>It should be done just like this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>/**\n * @param &lt;T&gt; This describes my type parameter\n */\nclass MyClass&lt;T&gt;{\n\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/docs/tooldocs/windows/javadoc.html#@param\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Source</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 14727,
      "reputation" : 1745,
      "user_id" : 30547,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0b69c0346a7eca8e898998e508f4264e?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Dave DiFranco",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/30547/dave-difranco"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 30,
    "last_activity_date" : 1369914990,
    "last_edit_date" : 1369914990,
    "creation_date" : 1262809921,
    "answer_id" : 2016007,
    "question_id" : 2015972,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Yes.\nJust use the @param tag, and include angle brackets around the type parameter.</p>\n\n<p>Like this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>/**\n *  @param &lt;T&gt; This describes my type parameter\n */\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 14429973,
      "reputation" : 3626,
      "user_id" : 10423604,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/W6A8i.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Volodya Lombrozo",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/10423604/volodya-lombrozo"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1709281568,
    "creation_date" : 1709281568,
    "answer_id" : 78086421,
    "question_id" : 2015972,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In accordance with the <a href=\"https://checkstyle.sourceforge.io\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Checkstyle</a> style guide, it is preferable to describe parameters and their generic types for methods or constructors separately:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>/**\n * Constructor.\n * @param data Data parameter description.\n * @param &lt;T&gt; Data type description.\n */\npublic &lt;T&gt; MyClass(final T data) {\n    this.data = data;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Note that we have two entries for the <code>data</code> parameter description. Otherwise, if you only leave <code>@param data Data parameter description.</code>, Checkstyle will raise a complaint:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-bash prettyprint-override\"><code>Number of javadoc parameters different than method signature (JavadocParameterOrderCheck)\nExpected @param tag for '&lt;T&gt;'. (JavadocMethodCheck)\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
